                     <interp inst="t18310630-38-person396" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
             were with me - Hughes said the prisoner had his shoes on; he denied it, but on the road to the watch-house he said of his own accord, that he had done it through distress, and was sorry for it, but he could not help it.</p>
               <p>Prisoner's Defence. I went out with two other men - they had a suspicion of me, and said I had stolen them, but nobody saw me steal them; I bought them of a man at the corner of Shoreditch church.</p>
